    tableOfContents: [{id: `intro`, title: `Introduction`}, {id: `when-switch`, title: `When Can You Switch?`}, {id: `switching-process`, title: `How to Switch Plans`}, {id: `coverage-differences`, title: `Coverage Differences`}, {id: `faqs`, title: `Frequently Asked Questions`}],
    sections: [{type: `paragraph`, content: `Many Medicare beneficiaries consider switching from Medicare Advantage to Original Medicare for greater flexibility in choosing healthcare providers. This guide explains timing, eligibility, and key considerations.`}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `When Can You Switch Plans?`, id: `when-switch`}, {type: `paragraph`, content: `You have specific windows to switch. The Annual Enrollment Period runs October 15 to December 7 each year. You can also switch if you experience a qualifying life event like moving out of plan service area.`}, {type: `list`, ordered: false, items: [`Annual Enrollment Period: October 15 - December 7`, `Qualifying life events: relocation, loss of coverage, marriage/divorce`, `Medicare Open Enrollment: January 1 - March 31 for certain situations`, `Initial Enrollment Period: within 3 months of turning 65`]}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `How to Switch Plans`, id: `switching-process`}, {type: `paragraph`, content: `Switching is straightforward. Contact Medicare directly at 1-800-MEDICARE, use Medicare.gov, or work with a licensed agent. Your Original Medicare coverage begins January 1 if you enroll by December 7.`}, {type: `list`, ordered: true, items: [`Review Original Medicare coverage details and costs`, `Enroll in Part B if needed and a Medigap supplement plan`, `Select a Part D prescription drug plan`, `Confirm your Medicare Advantage plan termination`, `Keep documentation of all enrollment confirmations`]}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `Coverage Differences Explained`, id: `coverage-differences`}, {type: `table`, headers: [`Factor`, `Medicare Advantage`, `Original Medicare`], rows: [[`Provider Network`, `Limited to plan network`, `See any Medicare-approved provider`], [`Prescription Drugs`, `Included in plan`, `Requires separate Part D plan`], [`Supplemental Coverage`, `Limited options available`, `Medigap plans strongly recommended`], [`Out-of-Pocket Max`, `Yes, typically $5,000-$6,700`, `No maximum limit`], [`Specialist Approval`, `May need referral`, `No referral required`]]}, {type: `callout`, calloutType: `info`, calloutTitle: `Important Tip`, calloutText: `Always enroll in a Medigap plan when switching to Original Medicare to avoid substantial out-of-pocket costs.`}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `Key Considerations Before Switching`, id: `considerations`}, {type: `paragraph`, content: `Before switching, verify your current doctors accept Original Medicare and assess total monthly costs including premiums, deductibles, and copays for both Original Medicare and supplemental coverage.`}, {type: `list`, ordered: false, items: [`Check if your doctors participate in Original Medicare`, `Compare total annual costs including all premiums and deductibles`, `Review prescription drug coverage availability in Part D plans`, `Consider switching sooner if facing medical needs requiring specialist care`, `Verify your current medications are covered by selected Part D plan`]}, {type: `faq`, faqs: [{question: `Can I switch back to Medicare Advantage?`, answer: `Yes, during the Annual Enrollment Period (Oct 15-Dec 7) or within a qualifying life event window.`}, {question: `Will switching affect my current coverage?`, answer: `Your MA plan ends and Original Medicare begins January 1. Coordinate timing to avoid gaps in coverage.`}, {question: `Do I lose coverage if I miss the deadline?`, answer: `Missed deadlines may result in late enrollment penalties or gaps in coverage. Contact Medicare immediately if needed.`}]}],
    faqs: [{question: `What's the best time to switch from Medicare Advantage?`, answer: `The Annual Enrollment Period (Oct 15-Dec 7) is ideal, allowing January 1 effective date for seamless transition.`}, {question: `Do I need a Medigap plan with Original Medicare?`, answer: `Not required, but strongly recommended. Original Medicare has no out-of-pocket maximum, making Medigap cost-effective.`}, {question: `Can I switch mid-year outside enrollment periods?`, answer: `Only with qualifying life events like moving, losing coverage, or specific eligibility changes. Otherwise, wait for Oct 15.`}],
