    tableOfContents: [{id: `intro`, title: `Introduction`}, {id: `what-covered`, title: `What Is Actually Covered`}, {id: `limitations`, title: `Key Limitations and Exclusions`}, {id: `comparison`, title: `Comparing Plans with This Benefit`}, {id: `faqs`, title: `Frequently Asked Questions`}],
    sections: [{type: `paragraph`, content: `Traveling abroad as a Medicare beneficiary requires understanding your coverage gaps. Medigap foreign travel benefits provide limited emergency care protection when you're outside the U.S.`}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `What Is Actually Covered`, id: `what-covered`}, {type: `paragraph`, content: `Medigap foreign travel emergency coverage applies only to emergency medical care needed during foreign travel. Coverage begins after you've paid a $250 deductible and typically covers 80% of eligible expenses.`}, {type: `table`, headers: [`Coverage Aspect`, `Details`], rows: [[`Emergency Care Only`, `Accidents, sudden illness, dental emergencies`], [`Coverage Duration`, `First 60 days per trip outside U.S.`], [`Maximum Benefit`, `Up to $250,000 lifetime limit`], [`Cost Share`, `20% coinsurance after $250 deductible`]]}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `Key Limitations and Exclusions`, id: `limitations`}, {type: `list`, ordered: false, items: [`Routine, preventive, or non-emergency care not covered`, `Pre-existing condition treatment may be excluded`, `Travel to countries with U.S. travel warnings not covered`, `Trips longer than 60 days abroad lose coverage`, `Care in U.S. territories and protectorates may not qualify`]}, {type: `callout`, calloutType: `info`, calloutTitle: `Critical Detail`, calloutText: `Only Plans C, D, F, G, M, and N include foreign travel emergency benefits. Plans A, B, K, and L do not offer this coverage.`}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `Comparing Plans with This Benefit`, id: `comparison`}, {type: `table`, headers: [`Plan`, `Includes Foreign Travel`, `Other Key Benefits`], rows: [[`Plan C`, `Yes`, `Covers Part A/B coinsurance`], [`Plan F`, `Yes`, `Most comprehensive coverage`], [`Plan G`, `Yes`, `Good value with lower premiums`], [`Plan A`, `No`, `Basic coverage only`]]}, {type: `paragraph`, content: `Plan F and G are the most popular options with foreign travel benefits. Plan G offers excellent value with lower premiums than Plan F while maintaining emergency travel coverage.`}, {type: `heading`, level: 2, text: `Planning Your International Travel`, id: `planning`}, {type: `list`, ordered: true, items: [`Verify your Medigap plan includes foreign travel benefits`, `Review the $250 deductible and 20% coinsurance requirements`, `Purchase supplemental travel insurance for non-emergency care`, `Keep receipts and documentation for all foreign medical expenses`, `Contact your insurer before traveling for claims details`]}, {type: `callout`, calloutType: `warning`, calloutTitle: `Important`, calloutText: `Foreign travel benefits are not a substitute for comprehensive travel insurance. Consider additional coverage for non-emergency care and medical evacuation.`}, {type: `faq`, faqs: [{question: `Does Medigap cover routine doctor visits abroad?`, answer: `No. Only emergency care is covered. Routine checkups and non-urgent treatment are excluded.`}, {question: `What happens after 60 days of foreign travel?`, answer: `Coverage ends. You'll pay 100% of medical costs unless you return to the U.S. and later travel again.`}, {question: `Are prescription medications covered abroad?`, answer: `Only if prescribed for emergency treatment. Regular medication refills abroad are not covered.`}]}],
